edu.snu.onyx.runtime.master.scheduler

Interface PendingTaskGroupQueue

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SingleJobTaskGroupQueue

    @ThreadSafe
 @DefaultImplementation(value=SingleJobTaskGroupQueue.class)
public interface PendingTaskGroupQueue
    Keep tracks of all pending task groups. Scheduler enqueues the TaskGroups to schedule to this queue. SchedulerRunner refers to this queue when scheduling TaskGroups.

    • Method Detail

      • enqueue

        void enqueue(ScheduledTaskGroup scheduledTaskGroup)
        Enqueues a TaskGroup to this PQ.
        Parameters:
        scheduledTaskGroup - to enqueue.

      • dequeue

        Optional<ScheduledTaskGroup> dequeue()
        Dequeues the next TaskGroup to be scheduled.
        Returns:
        an optional of the the next TaskGroup to be scheduled, an empty optional if no such TaskGroup exists.

      • onJobScheduled

        void onJobScheduled(PhysicalPlan physicalPlanForJob)
        Registers a job to this queue in case the queue needs to understand the topology of the job DAG.
        Parameters:
        physicalPlanForJob - the job to schedule.

      • removeTaskGroupsAndDescendants

        void removeTaskGroupsAndDescendants(String stageIdOfTaskGroups)
        Removes a stage and its descendant stages from this queue. This is to be used for fault tolerance purposes, say when a stage fails and all affected TaskGroups must be removed.
        Parameters:
        stageIdOfTaskGroups - for the stage to begin the removal recursively.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Checks whether there are schedulable TaskGroups in the queue or not.
        Returns:
        true if there are schedulable TaskGroups in the queue, false otherwise.

      • close

        void close()
        Closes and cleans up this queue.
